{"type":"text","timestamp":1775852634739,"sessionID":"ses_286f0e191ffefhAfcDY3aVnFTa","part":{"id":"prt_d79109393001l8ZhU4Tr7P5xDu","messageID":"msg_d79106932001uFnmCQG8GL0W6j","sessionID":"ses_286f0e191ffefhAfcDY3aVnFTa","type":"text","text":"## AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 - Archive Summary\n\n### **What Was Completed**\n\n#### Core JWT Implementation ✅\n- **JWT Manager** (`jwt.go` - 258 lines):\n  - RSA 2048-bit key pair generation\n  - JWT token generation with RS256 signing algorithm\n  - JWT token validation with signature and expiration checks\n  - Kubernetes Secret persistence (`agentcube-jwt-keys`)\n  - Fallback to in-memory keys when Secret access fails\n  - PEM encoding/decoding for keys\n\n#### Authentication Middleware ✅  \n- **JWT Middleware** (`middleware.go`):\n  - Bearer token extraction from Authorization header\n  - Token validation and session ID context storage\n  - 401 Unauthorized responses for missing/invalid/expired tokens\n  - Correlation ID logging for authentication failures\n\n#### API Integration ✅\n- **Handler Integration** (`handlers.go`):\n  - JWT token generation on session creation\n  - Token included in `CreateSessionResponse`\n  - Health check endpoint validates JWT manager status\n\n#### Type Definitions ✅\n- **JWT Claims Structure** (`types.go`):\n  - `JWTClaims` with `SessionID` field\n  - Standard JWT `RegisteredClaims`\n  - `CreateSessionResponse` with `Token` field\n\n#### Error Handling ✅\n- **JWT-Specific Errors** (`errors.go`):\n  - `ErrJWTSigningFailed` constant\n  - Structured error responses with appropriate HTTP status codes\n\n#### Comprehensive Testing ✅\n- **JWT Tests** (`jwt_test.go` - 861 lines, 22 test functions):\n  - Manager initialization (existing Secret, nil clientset)\n  - Token generation/validation scenarios\n  - Key generation and PEM parsing\n  - Secret operations (create, load, missing fields)\n  - Concurrent operations\n  - Security scenarios (expired tokens, invalid signatures, malformed tokens)\n\n- **Middleware Tests** (`middleware_test.go` - 567 lines, 19+ test functions):\n  - JWT authentication middleware\n  - Token validation (valid, missing, invalid, expired)\n  - Session ID context storage\n  - Error response formatting\n  - Signature verification\n\n---\n\n### **What Was Deferred**\n\n#### Security Testing ❌\n- Algorithm confusion attack tests\n- \"None\" algorithm attack prevention\n- Token tampering detection\n- Replay attack prevention\n\n#### Performance Testing ❌\n- Benchmark functions for token generation/validation\n- P99 latency verification (target: <10ms generation, <5ms validation)\n- Concurrent performance tests\n\n#### Integration Testing ❌\n- End-to-end JWT authentication flow tests\n- Token expiration lifecycle tests\n- Multi-request token persistence tests\n\n#### Documentation ❌\n- API documentation updates with JWT authentication\n- Usage examples (token generation, validation, authenticated calls)\n- Authentication flow diagrams\n- Error response documentation\n\n#### Advanced Features ❌\n- Key rotation support\n- Metrics collection (token operations, failures, latency)\n- JWT health check endpoint integration\n- Configuration support (custom expiration, Secret names)\n- Prometheus metrics export\n\n#### Code Quality ⚠️\n- **Test Failures**: Some existing middleware and session management tests are failing\n- **Missing JWT-Specific Error Structs**: Only `ErrJWTSigningFailed` constant implemented, not full error structs\n- **No Benchmark Functions**: Performance targets not verified\n\n#### Optional Enhancements ❌\n- Key rotation during deployment\n- Multiple key support for transition periods\n- Token refresh mechanisms\n- Session ID validation in middleware\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\n**Status**: Core JWT functionality implemented with solid test coverage, but advanced security, performance validation, and documentation remain incomplete.\n\n**Key Achievements**: Fully functional JWT authentication system with RSA signing, Kubernetes Secret persistence, and comprehensive unit tests for core functionality.\n\n**Key Gaps**: Missing security hardening tests, performance benchmarks, integration tests, and user-facing documentation. Some existing test failures need resolution.","time":{"start":1775852634737,"end":1775852634737}}}
